The paper deals with collaborative beamforming in wireless networks, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The performance analysis of the approach involves system-level considerations (SY) and signal processing (MM). Finally, the paper also deals with the impact of phase errors, which falls under the category of physical-layer fundamentals (PF).
